A) Product Search – Test Cases

1. Valid Product Search (Positive)
Steps:
Enter a valid product name (e.g., “T-shirt”) in search bar
Click search
Expected Result:
Relevant products are displayed
Results match the keyword

2. Partial Keyword Search (Positive)
Steps:
Enter partial keyword (e.g., “shirt” instead of full name)
Expected Result:
Products containing the keyword are shown
Search supports partial matching

3. Non-Existent Product Search (Negative)
Steps:
Enter random/non-existent keyword (e.g., “xyz123abc”)
Expected Result:
“No results found” message displayed
No irrelevant products shown

4. Special Characters Input (Edge Case)
Steps:
Enter special characters (e.g., “@#$%^&*”)
Expected Result:
System handles input gracefully
No crash or error page
Either no results or validation message

5. Empty Search Submission (Negative)
Steps:
Click search without entering input
Expected Result:
Either all products shown OR prompt to enter search term
No system error

6. Case Sensitivity Check (Edge Case)
Steps:
Search same product in different cases (e.g., “t-shirt” vs “T-SHIRT”)
Expected Result:
Same results returned
Search is case-insensitive


B) Add to Cart – Test Cases
1. Add Single Product to Cart (Positive)
Steps:
Open product page
Click “Add to Cart”
Expected Result:
Product added successfully
Cart count increases

2. Add Multiple Quantities (Positive)
Steps:
Select quantity >1
Click “Add to Cart”
Expected Result:
Correct quantity added
Cart reflects accurate total

3. Add Out-of-Stock Product (Negative)
Steps:
Attempt to add out-of-stock item
Expected Result:
Add to Cart disabled OR error message shown
Item not added

4. Add Without Selecting Required Variant (Negative)
Steps:
Open product with variants (size/color)
Click “Add to Cart” without selecting variant
Expected Result:
Validation message displayed
Product not added

5. Add Same Product Repeatedly (Edge Case)
Steps:
Add same product multiple times
Expected Result:
Quantity increments correctly
No duplicate line item issues

6. Add to Cart with Invalid Quantity (Edge Case)
Steps:
Enter invalid quantity (e.g., 0, negative number, very large number)
Click “Add to Cart”
Expected Result:
Proper validation message
System restricts invalid values
